The paper deals with scheduling for coordinated multi-point (CoMP) transmission, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The focus on exploiting channel asymmetry suggests a potential fit with systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MM) subcategories. Finally, the use of metrics and simulation results may also suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
